The paper describes a toolkit for transfer learning, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically mentions that the toolkit includes 17 transfer learning models, which suggests that it is likely to be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE).
